Hello?

91
00:05:24,854 --> 00:05:27,121
Dad?

92
00:05:43,305 --> 00:05:45,139
[ Indistinct conversations ]

93
00:05:54,149 --> 00:05:56,150
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

94
00:05:56,218 --> 00:05:58,219
Hey. Hi. Oh.

95
00:05:58,320 --> 00:05:59,654
[ Applause ]

96
00:05:59,755 --> 00:06:01,155
Thank you. Thank you.
[ Car horn honking ]

97
00:06:01,223 --> 00:06:03,825
Thank you. You too. Oh.
[ Air brakes hiss ]

98
00:06:03,926 --> 00:06:06,227
You got to be kidding me!

99
00:06:06,328 --> 00:06:08,429
Hey, we're stepping up
to retail politics now, man.

100
00:06:08,497 --> 00:06:09,797
Look at this.
[ Laughs ]

101
00:06:09,865 --> 00:06:11,966
No, seriously.

102
00:06:12,034 --> 00:06:13,501
You know, a town this small,

103
00:06:13,602 --> 00:06:15,303
the whole thing could
come down to, you know,

104
00:06:15,404 --> 00:06:17,138
getting a few more of your
people to show up at the polls,

105
00:06:17,239 --> 00:06:18,406
a few less of the other guy's.

106
00:06:18,507 --> 00:06:20,008
Got to get the vote out.

107
00:06:20,109 --> 00:06:21,609
In this thing?
Yeah.

108
00:06:21,677 --> 00:06:24,812
Dress for the job you want,
not the job you have.

109
00:06:24,880 --> 00:06:26,514
The job I want is sheriff,

110
00:06:26,582 --> 00:06:28,850
not '80s heavy-metal
lead singer.

111
00:06:28,951 --> 00:06:30,518
I think I'll take my own car.

112
00:06:30,586 --> 00:06:32,186
- Nah!
- Yeah.

113
00:06:32,288 --> 00:06:33,788
Aw.

114
00:06:33,889 --> 00:06:35,256
Look at this.
He's gonna take his own car.

115
00:06:35,324 --> 00:06:36,457
Man of the people.

116
00:06:36,558 --> 00:06:37,759
Thank you.

117
00:06:37,860 --> 00:06:41,129
[ Car horn honking ]

118
00:06:41,230 --> 00:06:45,566
Walt has rubbed off on you
more than you realize.

119
00:06:47,469 --> 00:06:48,603
- Hey.
Cady: - Hey.

120
00:06:48,704 --> 00:06:51,172
Cady, what brings <i>you</i> here?

121
00:06:51,240 --> 00:06:54,108
Oh, I just came to wish my
dad luck on the big day. Oh.

122
00:06:54,209 --> 00:06:55,376
Oh, he hasn't
come in yet today.

123
00:06:55,477 --> 00:06:56,844
That's weird.
I was just at his house,

124
00:06:56,946 --> 00:06:58,146
and there was no sign of him.

125
00:06:58,247 --> 00:07:00,181
Oh, maybe he stopped to vote.

126
00:07:00,249 --> 00:07:01,866
Why don't you have a cup of coffee
and wait for him?

127
00:07:01,986 --> 00:07:02,832
Oh, um...

128
00:07:02,952 --> 00:07:05,720
Thanks, but I promised Henry
I'd go get out the vote.

129
00:07:05,788 --> 00:07:08,656
You know, a lot of people
on the Res don't have cars,

130
00:07:08,757 --> 00:07:11,392
so I'm gonna shuttle them
to their polling places.

131
00:07:11,493 --> 00:07:13,461
See you guys later.

132
00:07:13,529 --> 00:07:18,700
[ Door opens, closes ]

133
00:07:22,237 --> 00:07:23,571
[ Object thuds ]

134
00:07:29,979 --> 00:07:31,145
Bob.

135
00:07:31,246 --> 00:07:32,246
Huh?

136
00:07:32,348 --> 00:07:34,315
How did you get in here?

137
00:07:34,416 --> 00:07:35,850
Through the front door.

138
00:07:35,951 --> 00:07:38,853
The front door has been locked
since 2:00 A.M.

139
00:07:38,954 --> 00:07:41,356
Well, I fell asleep
in the bathroom,

140
00:07:41,423 --> 00:07:44,525
and then I came out here
and everyone was gone,

141
00:07:44,626 --> 00:07:47,695
the door was locked,
and I fell asleep out here.

142
00:07:47,796 --> 00:07:49,864
After helping yourself
to some drinks.

143
00:07:49,932 --> 00:07:51,899
And food.

144
00:07:51,967 --> 00:07:53,935
Look, I didn't mean to steal
anything, Henry.

145
00:07:54,036 --> 00:07:55,536
You know that.
I just...

146
00:07:55,604 --> 00:07:58,272
There just wasn't anybody here
to serve me.

147
00:07:58,340 --> 00:08:01,909
Why did you not think to call
someone to come get you?

148
00:08:01,977 --> 00:08:04,946
Well, I would have called
my lady friend,

149
00:08:05,047 --> 00:08:08,616
but Yelena broke up with me,
if you can believe it.

150
00:08:08,717 --> 00:08:09,951
Heartbreak or no,

151
00:08:10,052 --> 00:08:12,220
you need to call someone
to come pick you up.

152
00:08:12,321 --> 00:08:14,789
[ Indistinct conversations ]

153
00:08:19,228 --> 00:08:22,030
I was starting to wonder
if you were even gonna show up.

154
00:08:22,131 --> 00:08:24,232
I just wanted to wait for
the lunch crowd to clear out.

155
00:08:24,333 --> 00:08:26,034
Yeah, makes sense.

156
00:08:26,135 --> 00:08:28,903
Any idea which way
things are leaning?

157
00:08:29,004 --> 00:08:31,305
I can't tell you
anything like that.

158
00:08:31,407 --> 00:08:32,640
You know that.

159
00:08:32,708 --> 00:08:34,442
Just one? [ Chuckles ]

160
00:08:34,543 --> 00:08:35,977
[ Chuckles ]

161
00:08:49,358 --> 00:08:51,826
Man: They took away
my driver's license

162
00:08:51,894 --> 00:08:53,795
on account of my vision.

163
00:08:53,896 --> 00:08:56,898
I didn't think I was
gonna be able to vote.

164
00:08:56,999 --> 00:08:58,599
Well, I'm happy to help.

165
00:08:58,700 --> 00:09:00,568
You know who I voted for?

166
00:09:00,636 --> 00:09:03,237
It's really none
of my business.

167
00:09:03,338 --> 00:09:06,174
Longmire!
[ Chuckles ]

168
00:09:06,275 --> 00:09:07,942
[ Music ]

169
00:09:08,010 --> 00:09:09,844
All right.
Now, you all know me.

170
00:09:09,912 --> 00:09:12,346
I'm an Indian,
and I'm proud of my heritage.

171
00:09:12,448 --> 00:09:16,150
So you must understand how
strongly I believe in this man

172
00:09:16,251 --> 00:09:19,487
when I say to you
we all need to forget the past.

173
00:09:19,555 --> 00:09:21,656
It's time to look to the future.

174
00:09:21,723 --> 00:09:25,326
The future has stepped out
of his patrol car as we speak.

175
00:09:25,427 --> 00:09:27,929
Give it up
for Mr. Branch Connally!

176
00:09:27,996 --> 00:09:29,263
Thank you.

177
00:09:29,364 --> 00:09:30,798
[ Cheers and applause ]

178
00:09:33,268 --> 00:09:36,771
Get 'em, big guy.

179
00:09:36,839 --> 00:09:39,207
Thank you very much.

180
00:09:39,274 --> 00:09:41,342
Think fast!

181
00:09:41,443 --> 00:09:43,711
Looking good, people.

182
00:09:43,812 --> 00:09:45,680
Vic: Hey, Henry.

183
00:09:45,747 --> 00:09:48,015
Thought you could use these.

184
00:09:48,117 --> 00:09:49,984
He was supposed to hand them out
to people,

185
00:09:50,085 --> 00:09:51,619
and I found them in a closet.

186
00:09:51,720 --> 00:09:53,287
Oh, yes. He preferred to run
a <i>silent</i> campaign.

187
00:09:53,388 --> 00:09:54,655
[ Scoffs ]

188
00:09:54,756 --> 00:09:55,890
Can I get you something to eat?

189
00:09:55,991 --> 00:09:57,225
Yeah, sure.

190
00:09:57,292 --> 00:09:58,693
I wouldn't mind
a little something.

191
00:09:58,794 --> 00:10:00,461
[ Cellphone rings ] Oh.

192
00:10:00,562 --> 00:10:01,963
Hey.

193
00:10:02,064 --> 00:10:03,564
Ferg: Hey, Vic.
Sorry to bug you.

194
00:10:03,665 --> 00:10:05,199
I didn't think I should bother
Branch or Walt.

195
00:10:05,300 --> 00:10:06,534
What's up, Ferg?

196
00:10:06,635 --> 00:10:08,369
Somebody just called in
a car accident.

197
00:10:08,470 --> 00:10:09,637
[ Sighs ] Sucks.

198
00:10:09,738 --> 00:10:11,072
[ Chuckling ] I know.

199
00:10:11,173 --> 00:10:12,907
And I got to stay here
Manning the phones

200
00:10:13,008 --> 00:10:14,675
until Ruby finishes
counting the votes.

201
00:10:14,743 --> 00:10:18,412
No, it's fine.
Tell me where I have to go.

202
00:10:18,480 --> 00:10:20,982
[ Music ]

203
00:10:46,108 --> 00:10:48,209
[ Crow caws ]

204
00:10:51,947 --> 00:10:53,948
[ Phone ringing ]

205
00:10:54,016 --> 00:10:55,416
Ferg:
Sheriff's station.

206
00:10:55,484 --> 00:10:56,784
Hey, Ferg.
It's me.

207
00:10:56,852 --> 00:10:58,753
So, I'm out here
at this accident site.

208
00:10:58,854 --> 00:11:01,789
It's the weirdest thing.

209
00:11:01,857 --> 00:11:03,724
It's like a double hit and run.

210
00:11:03,825 --> 00:11:05,560
Who'd you say called this in?

211
00:11:05,661 --> 00:11:07,094
Guy didn't leave his name.

212
00:11:07,196 --> 00:11:08,896
He just said he saw the wreck
as he drove by.

213
00:11:28,183 --> 00:11:32,753
Ferg, send an ambulance
right away, okay?

214
00:11:34,923 --> 00:11:37,225
Cady.

215
00:11:57,844 --> 00:12:01,142
Henry: [ Echoing ] Walt.
We just spoke to the head of trauma.

216
00:12:01,243 --> 00:12:03,311
She was unresponsive
when she came into the E.R.,

217
00:12:03,412 --> 00:12:04,879
so they rushed her
straight to surgery.

218
00:12:04,980 --> 00:12:06,647
Vic: [ Echoing ]
It's gonna be a few more hours

219
00:12:06,715 --> 00:12:07,915
depending on what they find.

220
00:12:07,983 --> 00:12:10,318
[ Monitor beeping ]

221
00:12:10,419 --> 00:12:12,019
[ Beeping intensifies ]

222
00:12:12,087 --> 00:12:14,255
[ Beeping stops ]

223
00:12:14,356 --> 00:12:16,257
Walt, did you hear
what we said?

224
00:12:16,358 --> 00:12:19,360
Lizzie: Oh, my God.

225
00:12:19,461 --> 00:12:21,929
I just heard.
She okay?

226
00:12:21,997 --> 00:12:24,832
I need to take a walk.

227
00:12:26,735 --> 00:12:28,402
Okay.

228
00:12:28,504 --> 00:12:31,272
Woman: <i>Oncology,</i>
<i>paging palliative services...</i>

229
00:12:31,373 --> 00:12:33,007
<i>Extension 3609.</i>

230
00:12:40,282 --> 00:12:42,783
[ Keys thud ] She okay?

231
00:12:42,885 --> 00:12:45,720
It's hard to say.
She was in surgery.

232
00:12:45,821 --> 00:12:47,955
It's pretty bad, though.

233
00:12:48,056 --> 00:12:50,424
Just wish there was something
we could do.

234
00:12:50,526 --> 00:12:53,094
Well, we could find
the son of a bitch who hit her.

235
00:12:53,195 --> 00:12:55,863
You're right.

236
00:12:55,964 --> 00:12:57,131
[ Sighs ]

237
00:12:57,199 --> 00:12:59,100
Looks like
you took some photos.

238
00:12:59,201 --> 00:13:00,601
Yeah.

239
00:13:00,702 --> 00:13:03,070
So, I went out there,
and as far as I can tell,

240
00:13:03,172 --> 00:13:05,406
Cady was out of the car
changing a flat tire.

241
00:13:05,474 --> 00:13:10,945
I found car Jack
and these lug nuts

242
00:13:11,065 --> 00:13:12,114
on the side of the road.

243
00:13:12,234 --> 00:13:17,285
Now, when the Pontiac
smashed into her wagon...

244
00:13:17,386 --> 00:13:21,822
[ Voice breaking ]
It must have sent her flying.

245
00:13:23,725 --> 00:13:25,259
It's okay, Ferg.

246
00:13:25,360 --> 00:13:28,062
How could somebody
do something like this

247
00:13:28,163 --> 00:13:30,231
and then just leave the scene?

248
00:13:30,299 --> 00:13:31,666
I know.

249
00:13:31,733 --> 00:13:34,502
[ Clears throat ]

250
00:13:34,570 --> 00:13:36,270
So, who owns that car?

251
00:13:36,371 --> 00:13:38,673
No plates, and I couldn't
get through the door,

252
00:13:38,740 --> 00:13:40,775
so I broke through
the passenger window

253
00:13:40,842 --> 00:13:42,643
and I checked
the glove compartment

254
00:13:42,744 --> 00:13:46,314
and found
a expired registration.

255
00:13:46,381 --> 00:13:50,484
Guy named Darren Tooman
in Montana is listed on it.

256
00:13:50,552 --> 00:13:52,920
<i>And</i> I found a fifth of bourbon

257
00:13:53,021 --> 00:13:55,423
on the front seat on the floor.

258
00:13:55,524 --> 00:13:57,258
Now, I know that with Ruby away

259
00:13:57,359 --> 00:13:58,826
somebody's supposed to be here,

260
00:13:58,927 --> 00:14:01,028
but I'm going to Montana to
find the owner of that car.

261
00:14:01,129 --> 00:14:03,764
Shoot.

262
00:14:03,832 --> 00:14:07,134
We got voicemail.
I'm going with you.

263
00:14:07,202 --> 00:14:08,769
[ Keys jingle ]

264
00:14:08,837 --> 00:14:10,605
[ Door closes ]

265
00:14:10,672 --> 00:14:13,507
Hey, Ferg.
No sticker?

266
00:14:13,575 --> 00:14:15,042
What?

267
00:14:15,110 --> 00:14:17,378
Don't forget to do
your civic duty today.

268
00:14:17,479 --> 00:14:18,813
I <i>am</i> doing my civic duty.

269
00:14:18,914 --> 00:14:20,214
Why's <i>he</i> so upset?

270
00:14:20,315 --> 00:14:22,183
Because his friend,
your ex-girlfriend,

271
00:14:22,284 --> 00:14:25,119
is in critical condition
after getting hit by a car.

272
00:14:25,220 --> 00:14:27,054
Cady?

273
00:14:27,122 --> 00:14:28,389
Yeah.

274
00:14:39,735 --> 00:14:41,902
[ Thunder rumbles ]

275
00:14:42,004 --> 00:14:44,805
Careful, Ferg.

276
00:14:44,906 --> 00:14:48,676
Paper on the windows can
sometimes mean meth house, okay?

277
00:14:51,480 --> 00:14:55,916
[ Humming ]

278
00:14:59,388 --> 00:15:00,988
[ Gun cocks ]

279
00:15:01,089 --> 00:15:02,757
Oh, shit!

280
00:15:02,858 --> 00:15:04,125
Ferg.

281
00:15:07,095 --> 00:15:08,596
Darren Tooman?

282
00:15:08,664 --> 00:15:09,697
Yeah?

283
00:15:09,765 --> 00:15:10,931
Get up.
Okay.

284
00:15:11,033 --> 00:15:13,267
Come on with us.

285
00:15:13,368 --> 00:15:16,037
I owned that Sprint
since high school,

286
00:15:16,138 --> 00:15:17,738
but it was just sitting
in the yard,

287
00:15:17,839 --> 00:15:19,240
so I sold it a few months ago.

288
00:15:19,308 --> 00:15:21,075
There's no record
of that sale, Darren.

289
00:15:21,143 --> 00:15:23,377
Well, I sold it on Craigslist.

290
00:15:23,478 --> 00:15:24,779
The guy paid cash.

291
00:15:24,880 --> 00:15:27,348
He kind of...
He overpaid, to be honest,

292
00:15:27,416 --> 00:15:28,849
but I sent in my part,

293
00:15:28,950 --> 00:15:31,285
the transfer of sale
to the state of Montana.

294
00:15:31,386 --> 00:15:33,387
But if the buyer didn't file
his paperwork,

295
00:15:33,488 --> 00:15:34,789
the sale never posted.

296
00:15:34,856 --> 00:15:37,224
That car is still
legally registered to you.

297
00:15:37,326 --> 00:15:41,028
Can you describe the guy
that bought the car, anything?

298
00:15:41,129 --> 00:15:44,598
'Cause if you don't, you might
be liable for manslaughter.

299
00:15:44,700 --> 00:15:47,301
Oh, well, he was a white guy,

300
00:15:47,402 --> 00:15:52,273
a brown baseball cap,
and he called himself "K-Dawg."

301
00:15:52,374 --> 00:15:54,675
[ Woman speaking indistinctly
over P.A. system ]

302
00:16:05,153 --> 00:16:07,855
Any news?

303
00:16:09,958 --> 00:16:12,760
No.

304
00:16:18,333 --> 00:16:21,569
Yeah... uh...

305
00:16:21,670 --> 00:16:23,437
Coffee or something?

306
00:16:26,074 --> 00:16:28,843
No.

307
00:16:28,944 --> 00:16:31,579
[ Man speaking indistinctly
over P.A. system ]

308
00:16:59,152 --> 00:17:01,186
Great. Great.
Thanks. Okay!

309
00:17:01,287 --> 00:17:03,689
K-Dawg, the guy who responded
to the Craigslist ad,

310
00:17:03,790 --> 00:17:05,290
is Kellen Dawes,

311
00:17:05,391 --> 00:17:07,960
and he lives in the county
right on the Montana border.

312
00:17:08,061 --> 00:17:09,595
Let's get there!

313
00:17:09,696 --> 00:17:12,397
Hey, Ferg. I know that you want
to do a good job for Walt,

314
00:17:12,498 --> 00:17:13,799
but you need to
take it down a notch.

315
00:17:13,866 --> 00:17:15,534
Why? Why do I need to take it
down a notch?

316
00:17:15,602 --> 00:17:17,135
I want to find this guy,
and I want to...

317
00:17:17,237 --> 00:17:19,871
And what?
You want to do <i>what?</i>

318
00:17:19,973 --> 00:17:21,406
You want to hurt him?

319
00:17:21,507 --> 00:17:22,908
Because if you go out there
like this, all jacked up,

320
00:17:23,009 --> 00:17:24,543
you're gonna do
something stupid.

321
00:17:24,611 --> 00:17:26,578
You're either gonna
get yourself in trouble

322
00:17:26,679 --> 00:17:28,814
or you're gonna get the bad guy
<i>out</i> of trouble.

323
00:17:28,881 --> 00:17:31,416
[ Sighs ] [ Keys jingle ]

324
00:17:31,517 --> 00:17:35,821
Maybe I should go talk
to Kellen Dawes by myself.

325
00:17:35,922 --> 00:17:37,789
[ Sighs ]

326
00:17:37,890 --> 00:17:40,225
Yeah.

327
00:17:40,326 --> 00:17:42,327
Yeah, maybe you should.

328
00:17:42,428 --> 00:17:45,664
[ Bag rustles ]

329
00:17:45,765 --> 00:17:47,966
It's gonna be okay.

330
00:17:50,937 --> 00:17:54,139
[ Door closes ]

331
00:17:54,240 --> 00:17:56,008
Man: [ Echoing ] You know,
it's supposed to be them

332
00:17:56,109 --> 00:17:59,077
sitting out here
and us in there.

333
00:17:59,145 --> 00:18:01,079
They're supposed to break
their leg on a trampoline

334
00:18:01,147 --> 00:18:03,148
or get stitches when their hand
slips carving a pumpkin,

335
00:18:03,249 --> 00:18:05,017
you know?

336
00:18:05,118 --> 00:18:09,254
[ Normal voice ] It's not
supposed to be like this.

337
00:18:09,355 --> 00:18:11,623
[ Clears throat ]

338
00:18:11,691 --> 00:18:13,592
[ Sighs ]

339
00:18:13,693 --> 00:18:16,128
My, uh, my son Troy,

340
00:18:16,195 --> 00:18:18,797
he's a football player,
a damn good one.

341
00:18:18,898 --> 00:18:21,533
And then suddenly
out of nowhere,

342
00:18:21,601 --> 00:18:23,835
he just starts losing
all this weight.

343
00:18:23,936 --> 00:18:25,804
[ Echoing ] I mean, it's crazy.

344
00:18:25,905 --> 00:18:27,673
Like 30 pounds in a few weeks.

345
00:18:27,774 --> 00:18:29,941
[ Normal voice ] And they
don't know what's wrong.

346
00:18:30,043 --> 00:18:31,510
Centuries of science

347
00:18:31,611 --> 00:18:35,147
and they can't tell me
what's wrong with my son.

348
00:18:35,248 --> 00:18:38,784
It's our fault.

349
00:18:40,453 --> 00:18:43,422
We're supposed
to take care of them.

350
00:18:45,358 --> 00:18:48,694
We forget to and start thinking
about ourselves.

351
00:18:48,795 --> 00:18:54,399
We go out
and have a good day...

352
00:18:54,500 --> 00:18:56,435
[ Exhales sharply ]

353
00:19:07,246 --> 00:19:10,415
Thinking
about our own happiness

354
00:19:10,516 --> 00:19:12,184
instead of theirs.

355
00:19:12,251 --> 00:19:15,721
The world decides
to even things out.

356
00:19:22,495 --> 00:19:25,230
Kellen Dawes?

357
00:19:25,331 --> 00:19:26,531
Yes?

358
00:19:26,632 --> 00:19:28,200
[ Gun cocks ]

359
00:19:28,267 --> 00:19:32,204
You mind putting the gun down,
showing me your hands?

360
00:19:32,271 --> 00:19:34,072
I do.

361
00:19:34,173 --> 00:19:36,441
But I will anyways.

362
00:19:43,082 --> 00:19:45,050
Thanks.

363
00:19:47,703 --> 00:19:49,437
That's a nice rifle.

364
00:19:49,538 --> 00:19:52,307
Only because I take care of it.

365
00:19:52,408 --> 00:19:54,909
I can see that.

366
00:19:54,977 --> 00:19:58,713
I'm more interested in a car,
an old Sprint.

367
00:19:58,814 --> 00:20:00,548
You know that car?

368
00:20:00,616 --> 00:20:01,983
'Course I do.

369
00:20:02,084 --> 00:20:03,752
Worst $500 I ever spent.

370
00:20:03,819 --> 00:20:06,821
And a couple weeks ago,
somebody stole it.

371
00:20:06,889 --> 00:20:09,157
Why didn't you
report it stolen?

372
00:20:09,258 --> 00:20:11,326
Why do you even care
about that stupid car?

373
00:20:11,427 --> 00:20:13,428
'Cause it was involved
in a hit and run.

374
00:20:13,529 --> 00:20:15,497
That's really too bad.

375
00:20:15,598 --> 00:20:17,065
Everybody okay?

376
00:20:17,166 --> 00:20:18,466
No.

377
00:20:18,534 --> 00:20:20,568
Well...

378
00:20:20,636 --> 00:20:22,637
I can tell you I didn't have
nothing to do with it.

379
00:20:22,738 --> 00:20:26,674
Then you won't mind me taking
a look around your property?

380
00:20:26,776 --> 00:20:28,610
Knock yourself out.

381
00:20:35,084 --> 00:20:38,186
[ Monitor beeping ]

382
00:20:44,894 --> 00:20:48,229
[ Alarm sounding ]

383
00:20:52,101 --> 00:20:53,735
[ Alarm continues ]

384
00:20:58,908 --> 00:21:01,376
[ Monitor beeps, alarm stops,
steady beeping continues ]

385
00:21:04,446 --> 00:21:07,715
Branch: So, what are we doing
to find the guy that hit Cady?

386
00:21:07,817 --> 00:21:11,719
What are <i>we</i> doing?

387
00:21:11,821 --> 00:21:14,189
Well, Vic and I
went to Montana and back,

388
00:21:14,290 --> 00:21:16,991
but I'm not really sure
what <i>you've</i> been doing.

389
00:21:17,092 --> 00:21:19,460
You... you pissed at me?

390
00:21:19,562 --> 00:21:23,631
Honestly, I've been pissed
at you for months now.

391
00:21:23,732 --> 00:21:26,067
Me?

392
00:21:26,168 --> 00:21:28,069
What'd I do?

393
00:21:28,170 --> 00:21:31,906
You could've dated <i>anybody.</i>

394
00:21:33,909 --> 00:21:36,477
Why'd it have to be Cady?

395
00:21:36,545 --> 00:21:39,180
[ Sighs ]

396
00:21:39,281 --> 00:21:42,150
Wow. Uh...

397
00:21:42,251 --> 00:21:45,520
I had no idea
that you even liked her.

398
00:21:45,621 --> 00:21:48,656
Yeah, well, there you have it.

399
00:21:50,759 --> 00:21:51,926
[ Sighs ]

400
00:21:52,027 --> 00:21:53,361
I don't know what to say.

401
00:21:53,462 --> 00:21:54,662
Just forget it.

402
00:21:57,666 --> 00:21:59,567
[ Clears throat ]

403
00:21:59,668 --> 00:22:00,935
[ Dog barks in distance ]

404
00:22:03,839 --> 00:22:05,440
[ Sighs ]

405
00:22:05,541 --> 00:22:08,743
Where'd they take the cars?

406
00:22:08,844 --> 00:22:10,111
Print shed.

407
00:22:14,350 --> 00:22:16,451
You want to come along?

408
00:22:16,552 --> 00:22:21,222
No, I got to... stay here
in case Vic calls.

409
00:22:28,664 --> 00:22:32,300
[ Door opens, closes ]

410
00:22:38,040 --> 00:22:40,775
[ Object rattles ]

411
00:22:40,843 --> 00:22:43,711
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

412
00:23:07,770 --> 00:23:11,572
She's gonna be okay, Walt.

413
00:23:23,385 --> 00:23:26,487
Uh...
[ Clears throat, sighs ]

414
00:23:26,588 --> 00:23:30,959
Thought you'd want to know
where we stand with the driver.

415
00:23:31,026 --> 00:23:36,531
The owner of record sold the car
to a guy named Kellen Dawes.

416
00:23:36,598 --> 00:23:41,970
Kellen says the car was stolen
a couple weeks ago.

417
00:23:42,037 --> 00:23:46,708
Whoever drove the car
left behind blood.

418
00:23:46,775 --> 00:23:50,678
There'd be cuts,
scrapes, worse.

419
00:23:50,779 --> 00:23:52,447
[ Sighs ]

420
00:23:52,548 --> 00:23:54,515
Kellen didn't have any
that I can see,

421
00:23:54,583 --> 00:23:56,284
so I'm inclined to believe him.

422
00:23:56,385 --> 00:23:59,520
Checked at all the hospitals

423
00:23:59,588 --> 00:24:02,056
to see if anyone's come in
with consistent injuries

424
00:24:02,157 --> 00:24:03,825
in the last 24 hours,
and, uh...

425
00:24:03,926 --> 00:24:06,828
Nothing.

426
00:24:06,929 --> 00:24:11,666
So I guess...

427
00:24:11,767 --> 00:24:15,370
That I'm nowhere.

428
00:24:15,471 --> 00:24:17,472
[ Beeping continues ]

429
00:24:20,409 --> 00:24:23,044
[ Voice breaking ]
I'm so sorry, Walt.

430
00:24:23,145 --> 00:24:25,713
Check the drug stores.

431
00:24:25,781 --> 00:24:28,182
Security cameras.

432
00:24:28,283 --> 00:24:33,354
Look for anybody who came in
to buy first-aid supplies...

433
00:24:33,422 --> 00:24:37,358
Gauze, bandages, disinfectant.

434
00:24:37,426 --> 00:24:39,093
After what they did,

435
00:24:39,161 --> 00:24:43,264
they'd stay away from hospitals,
doctor's offices.

436
00:24:43,332 --> 00:24:45,500
Okay.

437
00:24:49,972 --> 00:24:53,074
[ Beeping continues ]

438
00:24:53,142 --> 00:24:55,576
Hey, Walt.

439
00:24:55,677 --> 00:24:59,013
You won.

440
00:24:59,114 --> 00:25:01,215
What?

441
00:25:03,886 --> 00:25:06,521
The election.

442
00:25:09,491 --> 00:25:11,125
Oh.

443
00:25:39,988 --> 00:25:41,989
[ Sighs ]

444
00:26:02,044 --> 00:26:03,978
Vic: We must have
gone through

445
00:26:04,079 --> 00:26:06,747
half the pharmacy security tapes
in Montana.

446
00:26:06,815 --> 00:26:08,783
I got a couple left.
[ Sighs ]

447
00:26:08,884 --> 00:26:10,418
What are we supposed to do

448
00:26:10,519 --> 00:26:13,121
if our mystery driver had all
the first-aid stuff on hand?

449
00:26:13,222 --> 00:26:15,189
We're supposed to try
everything, right?

450
00:26:15,257 --> 00:26:16,657
No, I know.

451
00:26:16,725 --> 00:26:17,959
[ Key clacks ]

452
00:26:18,060 --> 00:26:19,193
Just seems like
a long-shot.

453
00:26:19,261 --> 00:26:21,796
I got one.
Check this out, Vic.

454
00:26:23,732 --> 00:26:25,032
Oh, my God.

455
00:26:25,134 --> 00:26:26,300
I know.

456
00:26:26,368 --> 00:26:28,002
Bandages,

457
00:26:28,103 --> 00:26:29,604
pain meds, ice packs.

458
00:26:29,705 --> 00:26:32,006
No, I know that guy.

459
00:26:32,074 --> 00:26:35,176
That's the kid that said
that his car was stolen.

460
00:26:35,277 --> 00:26:36,511
That's Kellen Dawes.

461
00:26:46,388 --> 00:26:48,489
Vic: Kellen?

462
00:26:48,590 --> 00:26:50,258
[ Door slams ]

463
00:26:50,325 --> 00:26:51,526
Kellen, stop!

464
00:26:55,230 --> 00:26:57,331
[ Grunts ]

465
00:26:59,768 --> 00:27:01,869
[ Panting ]

466
00:27:06,408 --> 00:27:08,709
What are you doing?

467
00:27:08,777 --> 00:27:10,378
I'm in Montana now.

468
00:27:10,479 --> 00:27:12,213
You don't have jurisdiction
over here.

469
00:27:12,314 --> 00:27:13,548
<i>That's</i> the state line?
Yeah.

470
00:27:13,615 --> 00:27:15,483
That's the state line
right there.

471
00:27:15,584 --> 00:27:16,717
How can you be so sure?

472
00:27:16,785 --> 00:27:18,786
I've lived here all my life.

473
00:27:18,887 --> 00:27:20,955
I know where the state line is.

474
00:27:21,056 --> 00:27:22,023
Yeah.

475
00:27:22,124 --> 00:27:23,491
Hey!

476
00:27:23,559 --> 00:27:25,626
[ Grunts ]

477
00:27:25,694 --> 00:27:26,827
Hey, you can't do this.

478
00:27:26,895 --> 00:27:28,362
You don't have authority
over here!

479
00:27:28,430 --> 00:27:30,198
You're overlooking one thing,
Kellen.

480
00:27:30,299 --> 00:27:32,400
I don't give a shit whether or
not I have authority in Montana.

481
00:27:32,501 --> 00:27:34,135
You hit a girl with your car
and you ran.

482
00:27:34,236 --> 00:27:36,704
You're under arrest!
It wasn't me. I swear.

483
00:27:36,805 --> 00:27:39,006
Then what were you doing
buying first-aid supplies

484
00:27:39,074 --> 00:27:40,975
at a pharmacy an hour
after the accident?

485
00:27:41,076 --> 00:27:42,243
It was for a friend!

486
00:27:42,344 --> 00:27:43,544
I loaned him my car!

487
00:27:43,612 --> 00:27:45,213
He came back all messed up.

488
00:27:45,314 --> 00:27:46,847
<i>What</i> friend?

489
00:27:46,949 --> 00:27:50,451
[ Both breathing heavily ]

490
00:27:53,255 --> 00:27:54,488
[ Tires skid ]

491
00:27:59,328 --> 00:28:00,995
Bob!

492
00:28:02,764 --> 00:28:03,864
Open up!

493
00:28:03,966 --> 00:28:07,902
Billy, where's your dad?

494
00:28:08,003 --> 00:28:09,003
He's not here.

495
00:28:09,071 --> 00:28:10,871
Ow!
You're hurting me!

496
00:28:10,973 --> 00:28:12,506
You're under arrest!
Get up!

497
00:28:12,608 --> 00:28:14,108
What?
What did I ever do?

498
00:28:14,176 --> 00:28:16,677
You hit my daughter with a car
and left her to die!

499
00:28:16,778 --> 00:28:18,546
Get in!

500
00:28:48,477 --> 00:28:51,112
How drunk were you?

501
00:28:51,213 --> 00:28:54,148
I wasn't. I swear.

502
00:28:54,250 --> 00:28:55,583
Bullshit.

503
00:28:55,684 --> 00:28:58,086
Found a fifth of bourbon
in the front seat,

504
00:28:58,187 --> 00:29:00,054
not to mention the fact
that you felt the need

505
00:29:00,155 --> 00:29:02,056
to flee the scene
of the accident.

506
00:29:02,157 --> 00:29:03,658
Nobody does that...

507
00:29:03,759 --> 00:29:05,894
Unless they have something
to hide, so...

508
00:29:05,995 --> 00:29:07,562
How drunk were you?!

509
00:29:07,663 --> 00:29:11,065
I told you...
I wasn't drunk.

510
00:29:11,166 --> 00:29:14,936
I mean...

511
00:29:15,037 --> 00:29:17,238
Not very.

512
00:29:17,339 --> 00:29:18,640
But I was okay to drive.

513
00:29:18,741 --> 00:29:21,676
My unconscious daughter...

514
00:29:21,777 --> 00:29:24,379
Would argue otherwise.

515
00:29:26,415 --> 00:29:29,617
My dad called me
from the Red Pony,

516
00:29:29,718 --> 00:29:32,320
and he asked me
for a ride home.

517
00:29:32,421 --> 00:29:33,922
And my car's in the shop,

518
00:29:34,023 --> 00:29:36,124
so I borrowed
my friend Kellen's.

519
00:29:36,225 --> 00:29:38,359
And while I was on my way over
to get dad,

520
00:29:38,460 --> 00:29:39,761
Kellen texted me.

521
00:29:39,862 --> 00:29:41,262
[ Sighs ]

522
00:29:41,363 --> 00:29:43,798
I didn't think it was
a big deal to read it, but...

523
00:29:43,899 --> 00:29:47,135
I must have taken my eyes
off of the road for a second.

524
00:29:47,236 --> 00:29:50,538
And that's when I hit
the parked car.

525
00:29:50,639 --> 00:29:52,540
I was dazed
'cause I hit my head.

526
00:29:52,641 --> 00:29:54,842
I didn't even see
your daughter at first.

527
00:29:54,944 --> 00:29:56,644
It wasn't until after I got out

528
00:29:56,745 --> 00:29:58,346
that I saw her
over in the grass.

529
00:29:58,447 --> 00:29:59,614
If you saw her...

530
00:29:59,715 --> 00:30:01,716
Why did you run?

531
00:30:01,817 --> 00:30:05,286
[ Sighs ]
I was sc... I was scared.

532
00:30:05,387 --> 00:30:07,722
You realize she could have died
if nobody found her?!

533
00:30:07,823 --> 00:30:09,390
[ Crying ]
I'm so sorry, sheriff.

534
00:30:09,491 --> 00:30:13,394
I did call 911.
I swear.

535
00:30:13,495 --> 00:30:16,164
Book him.

536
00:30:16,265 --> 00:30:18,900
Driving while intoxicated,

537
00:30:19,001 --> 00:30:21,336
reckless endangerment,

538
00:30:21,437 --> 00:30:24,639
driving an
unregistered vehicle,

539
00:30:24,740 --> 00:30:27,508
fleeing the scene
of an accident...

540
00:30:27,609 --> 00:30:30,778
And anything else
you can think of.

541
00:30:33,816 --> 00:30:36,584
[ Cellphone rings ]

542
00:30:36,685 --> 00:30:38,319
[ Sighs ]

543
00:30:38,420 --> 00:30:40,888
[ Birds chirping ]

544
00:30:40,990 --> 00:30:42,156
Branch: Yeah?

545
00:30:42,257 --> 00:30:43,358
Morning, Branch.

546
00:30:43,459 --> 00:30:44,892
Look, I know it sucks,

547
00:30:44,994 --> 00:30:47,328
but that was no way
to handle it.

548
00:30:47,429 --> 00:30:49,097
What are you talking about?

549
00:30:49,198 --> 00:30:51,232
I had a room
full of people, man,

550
00:30:51,333 --> 00:30:52,567
60 supporters of yours

551
00:30:52,668 --> 00:30:55,003
waiting to drown their sorrows
with you,

552
00:30:55,104 --> 00:30:56,738
and you don't even show up.

553
00:30:56,839 --> 00:30:59,207
Can't get you on the phone.

554
00:30:59,308 --> 00:31:01,342
Nobody likes
losing an election,

555
00:31:01,443 --> 00:31:03,745
especially not
by such a slim margin.

556
00:31:03,846 --> 00:31:05,580
How slim was it?

557
00:31:05,681 --> 00:31:07,849
You lost by 17 votes.

558
00:31:07,950 --> 00:31:09,550
And if you want to win
the next one,

559
00:31:09,651 --> 00:31:11,619
you're gonna have to learn
to give the people

560
00:31:11,720 --> 00:31:13,388
who helped you
a little more respect.

561
00:31:13,489 --> 00:31:16,257
Honestly, Jacob,

562
00:31:16,358 --> 00:31:18,559
I got bigger things
to worry about.

563
00:31:18,660 --> 00:31:21,229
[ Cellphone beeps ]

564
00:31:49,024 --> 00:31:51,692
[ Engine sputters, shuts off ]

565
00:31:55,497 --> 00:31:57,765
[ Footsteps approach ]

566
00:31:57,866 --> 00:31:59,934
[ Knock on door ]

567
00:32:03,072 --> 00:32:05,473
Walt, I've got to talk to you.

568
00:32:05,574 --> 00:32:07,008
It's about Billy.

569
00:32:12,948 --> 00:32:17,185
There's nothing I can do
for your son, Bob.

570
00:32:17,286 --> 00:32:19,120
He did a bad thing.

571
00:32:19,221 --> 00:32:22,256
There's gonna be consequences.

572
00:32:22,357 --> 00:32:25,660
Except he didn't.

573
00:32:25,761 --> 00:32:28,830
Billy didn't do
what he said he did.

574
00:32:28,931 --> 00:32:32,200
It was me.

575
00:32:32,301 --> 00:32:34,635
I was driving.

576
00:32:34,736 --> 00:32:37,038
I've been drinking
for a few days,

577
00:32:37,139 --> 00:32:39,140
and Yelena broke up with me,

578
00:32:39,241 --> 00:32:42,176
and... Billy came
to pick me up.

579
00:32:42,277 --> 00:32:45,012
But I made him let <i>me</i> drive.

580
00:32:45,114 --> 00:32:47,782
Trying to prove something
to him, I guess.

581
00:32:47,883 --> 00:32:49,617
Then...

582
00:32:53,388 --> 00:32:55,456
When we hit Cady's car...

583
00:32:55,557 --> 00:32:58,025
He told me to take off.

584
00:32:58,127 --> 00:33:00,027
Said he wasn't as drunk as me.

585
00:33:00,129 --> 00:33:01,362
Because of my record,

586
00:33:01,463 --> 00:33:03,498
I'd probably get
in more trouble.

587
00:33:03,599 --> 00:33:09,003
So you have to
arrest <i>me,</i> Walt...

588
00:33:09,104 --> 00:33:11,139
Not Billy.

589
00:33:11,240 --> 00:33:13,174
I did it.

590
00:33:16,278 --> 00:33:17,245
[ Yells ]

591
00:33:17,346 --> 00:33:19,680
[ Piano plays discordantly ]

592
00:33:24,186 --> 00:33:25,920
Get...

593
00:33:26,021 --> 00:33:28,022
Get up!

594
00:33:28,123 --> 00:33:30,992
Come on!

595
00:33:31,093 --> 00:33:35,263
You're coming with me.
Come on.

596
00:33:37,966 --> 00:33:39,367
[ Door closes ]

597
00:33:42,999 --> 00:33:47,036
There it is.
That's the car you hit.

598
00:33:47,137 --> 00:33:51,540
That's the car you were driving
before you walked away.

599
00:33:51,641 --> 00:33:54,076
Get in.

600
00:33:54,177 --> 00:33:57,112
Get in there behind the wheel.

601
00:33:57,180 --> 00:33:59,515
Tell me what happened.

602
00:34:05,288 --> 00:34:07,556
[ Door hinges creaking ]

603
00:34:07,624 --> 00:34:08,891
[ Grunting ]

604
00:34:13,363 --> 00:34:15,164
Walt: Stop.

605
00:34:21,504 --> 00:34:23,806
You didn't crawl out
of this wreck, Bob.

606
00:34:23,907 --> 00:34:26,141
[ Sighs ] Your son did.

607
00:34:26,242 --> 00:34:29,445
He was skinny enough and
panicked enough to tear free.

608
00:34:29,546 --> 00:34:31,246
He squeezed his way out.

609
00:34:31,348 --> 00:34:33,248
And this car was heading
<i>towards</i> the Red Pony,

610
00:34:33,350 --> 00:34:34,550
not <i>away</i> from it.

611
00:34:34,651 --> 00:34:36,418
Your son hadn't even
picked you up yet.

612
00:34:36,519 --> 00:34:38,120
[ Sniffles ]

613
00:34:38,188 --> 00:34:42,624
Now, tell me, Bob, how'd you
really get those cuts?

614
00:34:42,726 --> 00:34:44,326
These cuts are not
from yesterday.

615
00:34:44,427 --> 00:34:45,594
They're fresh.

616
00:34:45,695 --> 00:34:48,664
You tell me the truth, Bob.

617
00:34:48,732 --> 00:34:51,967
[ Crying ] When I found out...

618
00:34:52,068 --> 00:34:54,937
When I found out
you arrested [Kicks car]

619
00:34:55,005 --> 00:34:57,806
When you arrested Billy,
I had to do something!

620
00:34:57,907 --> 00:35:00,809
I had to do something!

621
00:35:00,910 --> 00:35:04,747
I mean, this whole damn thing
was my fault!

622
00:35:04,814 --> 00:35:07,082
If I wasn't such
a worthless drunk,

623
00:35:07,183 --> 00:35:10,119
Billy wouldn't have even been
in the same place!

624
00:35:10,186 --> 00:35:12,321
He wouldn't have even
been there!

625
00:35:12,389 --> 00:35:14,857
[ Sobbing ] Oh, God.

626
00:35:14,924 --> 00:35:17,359
[ Sobs ]

627
00:35:17,460 --> 00:35:20,129
And so [Sniffles]
I broke a bottle.

628
00:35:20,196 --> 00:35:23,832
I cut myself up because I wanted
to convince you...

629
00:35:23,933 --> 00:35:26,101
that I did this
to your daughter, Walt.

630
00:35:26,202 --> 00:35:27,970
<i>I</i> did it.

631
00:35:28,071 --> 00:35:30,672
I may not have been driving
the damn car,

632
00:35:30,740 --> 00:35:33,442
but I did this!

633
00:35:33,543 --> 00:35:37,346
It was <i>my</i> fault,
and I should be punished!

634
00:35:37,447 --> 00:35:39,048
Not Billy!

635
00:35:39,115 --> 00:35:42,684
[ Sobbing ] Please, God, Walt!

636
00:35:42,752 --> 00:35:46,121
[ Moans ]

637
00:35:46,189 --> 00:35:48,757
My life is over.

638
00:35:52,295 --> 00:35:55,164
And I have wasted it.

639
00:35:55,265 --> 00:35:57,232
[ Sniffles ]

640
00:35:57,300 --> 00:36:01,537
But don't let me ruin
my son's life.

641
00:36:01,638 --> 00:36:03,572
[ Sobs ]

642
00:36:03,673 --> 00:36:06,809
I deserve to be punished,
not Billy.

643
00:36:06,910 --> 00:36:09,278
[ Sobbing ]

644
00:36:12,348 --> 00:36:14,650
Ferg: Do we need to put this
in triplicate?

645
00:36:14,751 --> 00:36:16,418
No.
Just initial it.

646
00:36:16,486 --> 00:36:18,387
[ Door opens ]

647
00:36:27,864 --> 00:36:32,334
A signed confession
Bob Barnes was the driver.

648
00:36:32,402 --> 00:36:34,009
I got a signed confession
from Billy

649
00:36:34,129 --> 00:36:35,398
saying the same thing.

650
00:36:35,518 --> 00:36:38,941
He said/he said.
I believe Bob.

651
00:36:39,042 --> 00:36:42,678
Walt:
Release him, Ferg.

652
00:36:44,447 --> 00:36:46,048
No.

653
00:36:46,116 --> 00:36:47,816
I won't.

654
00:37:03,032 --> 00:37:04,233
[ Hinges squeak ]

655
00:37:04,300 --> 00:37:06,235
Dad?

656
00:37:06,302 --> 00:37:08,370
What's going on?

657
00:37:08,471 --> 00:37:10,472
Walt: Come on.

658
00:37:20,850 --> 00:37:23,051
[ Latch clicks ]

659
00:37:31,661 --> 00:37:32,961
[ Dog barks in distance ]

660
00:37:39,335 --> 00:37:42,871
[ Door opens, closes ]

661
00:37:45,742 --> 00:37:48,577
Branch, there's nothing
in the tread walls.

662
00:37:48,678 --> 00:37:50,245
You sure?

663
00:37:50,313 --> 00:37:52,114
It's practically
brand-new.

664
00:37:52,215 --> 00:37:53,916
I know.

665
00:37:54,017 --> 00:37:55,584
It's crazy.
[ Bell dings ]

666
00:37:55,685 --> 00:37:57,085
No nails, screws, nothing.

667
00:37:57,153 --> 00:37:58,487
[ Drill whirs ]

668
00:37:58,588 --> 00:38:00,022
You want to buy a new tire?

669
00:38:00,123 --> 00:38:01,590
No, I want to fix this one.

670
00:38:01,691 --> 00:38:02,858
Look, maybe...

671
00:38:02,959 --> 00:38:04,927
Maybe the leak's
not in the tread.

672
00:38:05,028 --> 00:38:07,329
Maybe... maybe
it's in the sidewall.

673
00:38:07,430 --> 00:38:09,698
All right.
[ Bell dings ]

674
00:38:09,799 --> 00:38:11,200
Man: Hey, come on.

675
00:38:11,301 --> 00:38:13,202
Listen, I got to go ring up
those customers.

676
00:38:13,303 --> 00:38:15,537
I'll be right back.

677
00:38:15,605 --> 00:38:17,773
Yeah, sorry for the wait.

678
00:38:17,874 --> 00:38:19,341
Let me go get that part.

679
00:38:37,060 --> 00:38:39,595
[ Squeaking ]

680
00:38:44,968 --> 00:38:47,402
[ Monitor beeping ]

681
00:38:47,503 --> 00:38:49,071
Hey, punk.

682
00:38:51,241 --> 00:38:53,175
[ Sighs ]

683
00:38:55,078 --> 00:38:57,913
[ Sighs ]

684
00:38:57,981 --> 00:39:00,315
I thought if I could...

685
00:39:00,416 --> 00:39:03,252
if I could figure out
who hit you,

686
00:39:03,353 --> 00:39:06,722
I can find who to blame...

687
00:39:06,789 --> 00:39:09,858
that would somehow fix this.

688
00:39:12,629 --> 00:39:16,431
And here you still are.

689
00:39:16,532 --> 00:39:19,434
I haven't fixed anything.

690
00:39:24,340 --> 00:39:28,577
They say this is all
a horrible accident.

691
00:39:28,678 --> 00:39:32,314
This wasn't an accident.

692
00:39:34,217 --> 00:39:37,853
This is because of me.

693
00:39:48,965 --> 00:39:53,535
I found Bob Barnes in here
yesterday morning...

694
00:39:53,636 --> 00:39:55,070
Drunk.

695
00:39:55,138 --> 00:39:57,973
I told him to call someone
to come pick him up.

696
00:39:58,074 --> 00:40:02,044
I-I keep thinking...

697
00:40:02,145 --> 00:40:03,712
What if I had
driven him home myself?

698
00:40:03,813 --> 00:40:05,080
If I had just...

699
00:40:05,181 --> 00:40:07,149
This isn't about
any of that, Henry.

700
00:40:07,250 --> 00:40:10,752
This is <i>our</i> fault.

701
00:40:10,820 --> 00:40:13,255
You don't do what we did
in Denver

702
00:40:13,356 --> 00:40:15,724
without there being
consequences.

703
00:40:22,899 --> 00:40:25,400
I need to make things right.

704
00:40:25,468 --> 00:40:28,904
You cannot confess to a crime
you did not commit.

705
00:40:29,005 --> 00:40:31,440
I'm not talking
about confessing.

706
00:40:31,541 --> 00:40:34,976
I need to set things straight
with the world.

707
00:40:35,078 --> 00:40:37,079
With myself.

708
00:40:39,382 --> 00:40:41,483
With Cady.

709
00:40:41,551 --> 00:40:44,319
I've been selfish.

710
00:40:44,420 --> 00:40:48,190
I have to make a sacrifice.

711
00:40:50,093 --> 00:40:52,194
What are you saying?

712
00:40:52,295 --> 00:40:54,629
I need eagle feathers.

713
00:40:57,567 --> 00:40:59,668
I need your blessing
to do something

714
00:40:59,736 --> 00:41:01,903
a white man is not
supposed to do.

715
00:41:04,807 --> 00:41:07,242
No.

716
00:41:10,446 --> 00:41:13,682
I need to do this, Henry.

717
00:41:13,750 --> 00:41:17,919
There's nothing else I <i>can</i> do.

718
00:41:22,458 --> 00:41:25,894
Henry: We are nothing
but flesh and muscle...

719
00:41:25,995 --> 00:41:29,831
bones and blood.

720
00:41:29,932 --> 00:41:32,367
It is all we have to give.

721
00:41:44,080 --> 00:41:45,914
It is good you made
this vision quest

722
00:41:46,015 --> 00:41:49,384
to help your daughter.

723
00:41:49,485 --> 00:41:52,921
You will suffer...

724
00:41:53,022 --> 00:41:56,124
and shed blood
for the one you love.

725
00:41:58,127 --> 00:42:01,163
This is honorable.

726
00:42:04,133 --> 00:42:06,268
Her suffering
will not be in vain

727
00:42:06,369 --> 00:42:09,838
as long as you maintain your
focus on the healing vision.

728
00:42:24,654 --> 00:42:28,023
[ Thunder crashes ]

729
00:42:28,124 --> 00:42:30,625
You will return
to the umbilical connection

730
00:42:30,726 --> 00:42:32,861
to mother earth
with this piercing.

731
00:42:32,929 --> 00:42:34,863
Your communication with Maheyo

732
00:42:34,931 --> 00:42:37,299
will be through the love
of our mother.

733
00:42:37,400 --> 00:42:38,934
This way, your own thoughts

734
00:42:39,035 --> 00:42:41,136
will not cloud
the healing vision.

735
00:42:41,204 --> 00:42:45,273
Your sacrifice
will be made tangible

736
00:42:45,374 --> 00:42:48,443
through the shedding
of your blood and body.

737
00:42:48,544 --> 00:42:51,847
Your silence will be heard.

738
00:42:54,116 --> 00:42:57,919
[ Chanting loudly ]

739
00:42:58,020 --> 00:43:00,388
[ Thunder crashing ]

740
00:43:00,490 --> 00:43:04,192
[ Chanting echoing ]

741
00:43:07,330 --> 00:43:08,563
[ Wind whistling ]

742
00:43:08,664 --> 00:43:12,234
[ Chanting echoing ]

743
00:43:12,915 --> 00:43:15,289
